{"word":"κυκλόω","slug":"κυκλόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κυκλόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:κύκλος'><el>κύκλος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to encircle, surround</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—so in <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be surrounded</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to move in a circle, whirl round</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> or <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to go in a circle, go round</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to form into a circle</i>, <el>τόξα</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, of a bow, <i>to form a circle</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:confer, compare'>cf.</a> <el>κυκλοτερής.</el><p/></div>"}]}